{
  "texts": [
    "For 3DFlowAction [62], which relies on segmentation masks, we supply ground-truth masks due to frequent failures of the original mask estimator.Performance.",
    "Fig. 7 shows that all methods below 10B parameters-except TraceGen (0.67B)-fail to produce.",
    "Success rate vs. inference efficiency (predictions per minute; higher and rightward is better).TraceGen achieves the best combination of success and efficiency, outperforming both video and trace-based baselines by a large margin.",
    "Gains stem from its strong 3D motion prior and a lightweight warm-up in trace space via TraceForge.",
    "In contrast, video-generation baselines (e.g., NovaFlow or video backbone in AVDC) offer no practical few-shot warm-up path in our setting, and several trace baselines rely on object detectors or heuristic object filtering, making warm-up technically difficult."
  ]
}